{"orig":"/Users/kalaverin/src/lang/nim/lib/pure/rationals.nim","nimble":"stdlib","moduleDescription":"This module implements rational numbers, consisting of a numerator and a denominator. The denominator can not be 0.","entries":[{"name":"Rational","type":"skType","line":28,"col":18,"code":"Rational[T] = object\n  num*, den*: T","description":"A rational number, consisting of a numerator <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">num</span></span></tt> and a denominator <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">den</span></span></tt>."},{"name":"reduce","type":"skProc","line":32,"col":0,"code":"func reduce[T: SomeInteger](x: var Rational[T])","signature":{"arguments":[{"name":"x","type":"var Rational[T]"}],"genericParams":[{"name":"T","types":"SomeInteger"}]},"description":"<p>Reduces the rational number <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">x</span></span></tt>, so that the numerator and denominator have no common divisors other than 1 (and -1). If <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">x</span></span></tt> is 0, raises <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">DivByZeroDefect</span></span></tt>.</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> This is called automatically by the various operations on rationals.</p>\n"},{"name":"initRational","type":"skProc","line":54,"col":0,"code":"func initRational[T: SomeInteger](num, den: T): Rational[T]","signature":{"return":"Rational[T]","arguments":[{"name":"num","type":"T"},{"name":"den","type":"T"}],"genericParams":[{"name":"T","types":"SomeInteger"}]},"description":"<p>Creates a new rational number with numerator <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">num</span></span></tt> and denominator <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">den</span></span></tt>. <tt class=\"docutils litera