n</span></span></tt> (default is the largest possible <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">int</span></span></tt> for maximal resolution).</p>\n<p>The algorithm is based on the theory of continued fractions.</p>\n"},{"name":"toFloat","type":"skProc","line":116,"col":0,"code":"func toFloat[T](x: Rational[T]): float","signature":{"return":"float","arguments":[{"name":"x","type":"Rational[T]"}],"genericParams":[{"name":"T"}]},"description":"Converts a rational number <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">x</span></span></tt> to a <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">float</span></span></tt>."},{"name":"toInt","type":"skProc","line":120,"col":0,"code":"func toInt[T](x: Rational[T]): int","signature":{"return":"int","arguments":[{"name":"x","type":"Rational[T]"}],"genericParams":[{"name":"T"}]},"description":"Converts a rational number <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">x</span></span></tt> to an <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">int</span></span></tt>. Conversion rounds towards 0 if <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">x</span></span></tt> does not contain an integer value."},{"name":"`+`","type":"skProc","line":125,"col":0,"code":"func `+`[T](x, y: Rational[T]): Rational[T]","signature":{"return":"Rational[T]","arguments":[{"name":"x","type":"Rational[T]"},{"name":"y","type":"Rational[T]"}],"genericParams":[{"name":"T"}]},"description":"Adds two rational numbers."},{"name":"`+`","type":"skProc","line":132,"col":0,"code":"func `+`[T](x: Rational[T]; y: T): Rational[T]","signature":{"return":"Rational[T]","arguments":[{"name":"x","type":"Rational[T]"},{"name":"y","type":"T"}],"genericParams":[{"name":"T"}]},"description":"Adds the rational <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">x</span></span></tt> to the int <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">y</span></span></tt>."},{"name":"`+`","type":"skProc","line":137,"col":0,"code":"func `+`[T](x: T; y: Rational[T]): Rational[T]","signature":{"return":"Rational[T]","arguments":[{"name":"x","type":"T"},{"name":"y","type":"Rational[T]"}],"genericParams":[{"name":"T"}]},"description":"Adds the int <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">x</span></span></tt> to the rational <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">y</span></span></tt>."},{"name":"`+=`","type":"skProc","line":142,"col":0,"code":"func `+=`[T](x: var Rational[T]; y: Rational[T])","signature":{"arguments":[{"name":"x","type":"var Rational[T]"},{"name":"y","type":"Rational[T]"}],"genericParams":[{"name":"T"}]},"description":"Adds the rational <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">y</span></span></tt> to the rational <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">x</span></span></tt> in-place."},{"name":"`+=`","type":"skProc","line":149,"col":0,"code":"func `+=`[T](x: var Rational[T]; y: T)","signature":{"arguments":[{"name":"x","type":"var Rational[T]"},{"name":"y","type":"T"}],"genericParams":[{"name":"T"}]},"description":"Adds the int <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">y</span></span></tt> to the rational <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">x</span></span></tt> in-place."},{"name":"`-`","type":"skProc","line":153,"col":0,"code":"func `-`[T](x: Rational[T]): Rational[T]","signature":{"return":"Rational[T]","arguments":[{"name":"x","type":"Rational[T]"}],"genericParams":[{"name":"T"}]},"description":"Unary minus for rational numbers."},{"name":"`-`","type":"skProc","line":158,"col":0,"code":"func `-`[T](x, y: Rational[T]): Rational[T]","signature":{"return":"Rational[T]","arguments