ational[T]; y: T)","signature":{"arguments":[{"name":"x","type":"var Rational[T]"},{"name":"y","type":"T"}],"genericParams":[{"name":"T"}]},"description":"Multiplies the rational <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">x</span></span></tt> by the int <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">y</span></span></tt> in-place."},{"name":"reciprocal","type":"skProc","line":215,"col":0,"code":"func reciprocal[T](x: Rational[T]): Rational[T]","signature":{"return":"Rational[T]","arguments":[{"name":"x","type":"Rational[T]"}],"genericParams":[{"name":"T"}]},"description":"Calculates the reciprocal of <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">x</span></span></tt> (<tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"DecNumber\">1</span><span class=\"Operator\">/</span><span class=\"Identifier\">x</span></span></tt>). If <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">x</span></span></tt> is 0, raises <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">DivByZeroDefect</span></span></tt>."},{"name":"`/`","type":"skProc","line":227,"col":0,"code":"func `/`[T](x, y: Rational[T]): Rational[T]","signature":{"return":"Rational[T]","arguments":[{"name":"x","type":"Rational[T]"},{"name":"y","type":"Rational[T]"}],"genericParams":[{"name":"T"}]},"description":"Divides the rational <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">x</span></span></tt> by the rational <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">y</span></span></tt>."},{"name":"`/`","type":"skProc","line":233,"col":0,"code":"func `/`[T](x: Rational[T]; y: T): Rational[T]","signature":{"return":"Rational[T]","arguments":[{"name":"x","type":"Rational[T]"},{"name":"y","type":"T"}],"genericParams":[{"name":"T"}]},"description":"Divides the rational <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">x</span></span></tt> by the int <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">y</span></span></tt>."},{"name":"`/`","type":"skProc","line":239,"col":0,"code":"func `/`[T](x: T; y: Rational[T]): Rational[T]","signature":{"return":"Rational[T]","arguments":[{"name":"x","type":"T"},{"name":"y","type":"Rational[T]"}],"genericParams":[{"name":"T"}]},"description":"Divides the int <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">x</span></span></tt> by the rational <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">y</span></span></tt>."},{"name":"`/=`","type":"skProc","line":245,"col":0,"code":"func `/=`[T](x: var Rational[T]; y: Rational[T])","signature":{"arguments":[{"name":"x","type":"var Rational[T]"},{"name":"y","type":"Rational[T]"}],"genericParams":[{"name":"T"}]},"description":"Divides the rational <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">x</span></span></tt> by the rational <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">y</span></span></tt> in-place."},{"name":"`/=`","type":"skProc","line":251,"col":0,"code":"func `/=`[T](x: var Rational[T]; y: T)","signature":{"arguments":[{"name":"x","type":"var Rational[T]"},{"name":"y","type":"T"}],"genericParams":[{"name":"T"}]},"description":"Divides the rational <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">x</span></span></tt> by the int <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">y</span></span></tt> in-place."},{"name":"cmp","type":"skProc","line":256,"col":0,"code":"func cmp(x, y: Rational): int","signature":{"return":"int","arguments":[{"name":"x","type":"Rational"},{"name":"y","type":"Rational"}],"genericParams":[{"name":"Rational","types":"Rational[any]"}]},"description":"Compares two rationals. Returns<ul class=\"simple\"><li>a value less than zero, if <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">x</span> <span class=\"Operator\">&lt;</span> <span class=\"Identifier\">y</span></span></tt></li>\n<li>a value greater than zero, if <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">x</span> <span class=\"Operator\">&gt;</span> <span class=\"Identifier\">y</span></span></tt></li>\n<li>zero, if <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">x</span> <span class=\"Operator\">==</span> <span class=\"Identifier\">y</span></span></tt></li>\n</ul>\n"},{"name":"`&lt;`","type":"skProc","line":263,"col":0,"code":"func `<`(x, y: Rational): bool","signature":{"return":"bool","arguments":[{"name":"x","type":"Rational"},{"name":"y","type":"Rational"}],"genericParams":[{"name":"Rational","types":"Rational[any]"}]},"description":"Returns true if <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">x</span></span></tt> is less than <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">y</span></span></tt>."},{"name":"`&lt;=`","type":"skProc","line":267,"col":0,"code":"func `<=`(x, y: Rational): bool","signature":{"return":"bool","arguments":[{"name":"x","type":"Rational"},{"name":"y","type":"Rational"}],"genericParams":[{"name":"Rational","types":"Rational[any]"}]},"description":"Returns tue if <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">x</span></span></tt> is less than or equal to <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">y</span></span></tt>."},{"name":"`==`","type":"skProc","line":271,"col":0,"code":"func `==`(x, y: Rational): bool","signature":{"return":"bool","arguments":[{"name":"x","type":"Rational"},{"name":"y","type":"Rational"}],"genericParams":[{"name":"Rational","types":"Rational[any]"}]},"description":"Compares two rationals for equality."},{"name":"abs","type":"skProc","line":275,"col":0,"code":"func abs[T](x: Rational[T]): Rational[T]","signature":{"return":"Rational[T]","arguments":[{"name":"x","type":"Rational[T]"}],"genericParams":[{"name":"T"}]},"description":"Returns the absolute value of <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">x</span></span></tt>."},{"name":"`div`","type":"skProc","line":284,"col":0,"code":"func `div`[T: SomeInteger](x, y: Rational[T]): T","signature":{"return":"T","arguments":[{"name":"x","type":"Rational[T]"},{"name":"y","type":"Rational[T]"}],"genericParams":[{"name":"T","types":"SomeInteger"}]},"description":"Computes the rational truncated division."},{"name":"`mod`","type":"skProc","line":288,"col":0,"code":"func `mod`[T: SomeInteger](x, y: Rational[T]): Rational[T]","signature":{"return":"Rational[T]","arguments":[{"name":"x","type":"Rational[T]"},{"name":"y","type":"Rational[T]"}],"genericParams":[{"name":"T","types":"SomeInteger"}]},"description":"Computes the rational modulo by truncated division (remainder). This is same as <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">x</span> <span class=\"Operator\">-</span> <span class=\"Punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"Identifier\">x</span> <span class=\"Keyword\">div</span> <span class=\"Identifier\">y</span><span class=\"Punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"Operator\">*</span> <span class=\"Identifier\">y</span></span></tt>."},{"name":"floorDiv","type":"skProc","line":294,"col":0,"code":"func floorDiv[T: SomeInteger](x, y: Rational[T]): T","signature":{"return":"T","arguments":[{"name":"x","type":"Rational[T]"},{"name":"y","type":"Rational[T]"}],"genericParams":[{"name":"T","types":"SomeInteger"}]},"description":"<p>Computes the rational floor division.</p>\n<p>Floor division is conceptually defined as <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">floor</span><span class=\"Punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"Identifier\">x</span> <span class=\"Operator\">/</span> <span class=\"Identifier\">y</span><span class=\"Punctuation\">)</span></span></tt>. This is different from the <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Keyword\">div</span></span></tt> operator, which is defined as <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">trunc</span><span class=\"Punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"Identifier\">x</span> <span class=\"Operator\">/</span> <span class=\"Identifier\">y</span><span class=\"Punctuation\">)</span></span></tt>. That is, <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Keyword\">div</span></span></tt> rounds towards 0 and <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">floorDiv</span></span></tt> rounds down.</p>\n"},{"name":"floorMod","type":"skProc","line":303,"col":0,"code":"func floorMod[T: SomeInteger](x, y: Rational[T]): Rational[T]","signature":{"return":"Rational[T]","arguments":[{"name":"x","type":"Rational[T]"},{"name":"y","type":"Rational[T]"}],"genericParams":[{"name":"T","types":"SomeInteger"}]},"description":"<p>Computes the rational modulo by floor division (modulo).</p>\n<p>This is same as <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">x</span> <span class=\"Operator\">-</span> <span class=\"Identifier\">floorDiv</span><span class=\"Punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"Identifier\">x</span><span class=\"Punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"Identifier\">y</span><span class=\"Punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"Operator\">*</span> <span class=\"Identifier\">y</span></span></tt>. This func behaves the same as the <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Operator\">%</span></span></tt> operator in Python.</p>\n"},{"name":"hash","type":"skProc","line":311,"col":0,"code":"func hash[T](x: Rational[T]): Hash","signature":{"return":"Hash","arguments":[{"name":"x","type":"Rational[T]"}],"genericParams":[{"name":"T"}]},"description":"Computes the hash for the rational <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">x</span></span></tt>."},{"name":"`^`","type":"skProc","line":322,"col":0,"code":"func `^`[T: SomeInteger](x: Rational[T]; y: T): Rational[T]","signature":{"return":"Rational[T]","arguments":[{"name":"x","type":"Rational[T]"},{"name":"y","type":"T"}],"genericParams":[{"name":"T","types":"SomeInteger"}]},"description":"<p>Computes <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">x</span></span></tt> to the power of <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">y</span></span></tt>.</p>\n<p>The exponent <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">y</span></span></tt> must be an integer. Negative exponents are supported but floating point exponents are not.</p>\n"}]}